      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically robust 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2). This wide-body variant features the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus, delivering power through a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle and a viscous-coupling AWD system. Significant preventative measures have been addressed, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a new rear main seal (RMS). The chassis retains its factory-specified kinematic properties, offering precise turn-in and high-speed stability. Braking performance is optimized via four-piston monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors. This specimen represents a highly communicative driver\u2019s car with a linear torque curve and a taut, well-damped suspension setup.",
